<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1436,279,448]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
This Brazilian species was not studied in this work. In its original description, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bagnall" authorityYear="1924" box="[1044,1149,280,304]" class="Insecta" family="Thysanoptera (awaiting allocation)" genus="Phrasterothrips" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="affinis">
<emphasis box="[1044,1149,280,304]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">H. affinis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is considered close to 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Holopothrips" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="omercooperi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">H. omercooperi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, being distinguished mostly by having shorter head, longer postocular setae and reduced am setae, besides few other minute differences (
<bibRefCitation box="[578,734,351,376]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" refId="ref58216" refString="Bagnall, R. S. (1924) Brief descriptions of new Thysanoptera XIV. Annals and Magazine of Natural History, 14 (9), 625 - 640. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222932408633174" type="journal article">Bagnall 1924</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation box="[753,1042,351,376]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" refId="ref59437" refString="Mound, L. A. &amp; Marullo, R. (1996) The thrips of Central and South America: an introduction (Insecta: Thysanoptera). Memoirs on Entomology, International, 6, 1 - 488." type="journal article">Mound &amp; Marullo (1996)</bibRefCitation>
distinguished these two species by the occurrence of male pore plates, which are present on sternites VIâ€“VIII in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bagnall" authorityYear="1924" box="[1025,1130,388,412]" class="Insecta" family="Thysanoptera (awaiting allocation)" genus="Phrasterothrips" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="affinis">
<emphasis box="[1025,1130,388,412]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">H. affinis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but only in sternite VIII in 
<taxonomicName box="[151,327,425,448]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Holopothrips" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="omercooperi">
<emphasis box="[151,327,425,448]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">H. omercooperi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
